    "recap_headline": "Marshall University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "Buy Tickets Here\n|\nBox Score (PDF)\n|\nChampionship Fund\nHUNTINGTON, W.Va. \u2013\nThe Marshall University Baseball team (11-8, 3-0 SBC) completed a sweep of the Georgia State Panthers on Sunday at Jack Cook Field, 13-7, by overcoming a six-run deficit and scoring 13 unanswered runs.\nThe sweep marked the Herd's first conference-opening series sweep since 1995, when it swept Furman.\n\"It's great to open up conference play this way and be 3-0,\" Herd Baseball Head Coach\nGreg Beals\nsaid. \"I'm really proud of our guys and how they competed today. We got big hits when we needed to. Kamerer, Bottone, Smith, Harthan (had big hits).\nLanden Doll\nI think is the real story. Settling the game down putting zeros up in the middle of the game.\"\nAfter coming on in relief of starter\nKenyon Collins\n,\nLanden Doll\nissued just two hits while striking out seven in 4.0 innings to earn his second win of the season out of the bullpen.\nAt the plate,\nJackson Golden\n,\nEvan Bottone\nand\nTyler Kamerer\nall had multi-hit efforts with Bottone and Kamerer each homering. Bottone led the way with four RBI as\nJack Smith\nrecorded his second straight three-RBI contest.\nThe Panthers rattled off the first six runs of the game with five in the second and one in the third.\nHowever, in the bottom of the third,\nJackson Golden\nled off with a double and was moved over to third on a Bottone groundout. After taking a ball for the first pitch of his at bat, Kamerer smoked his second homer of the season to left to cut the deficit to 6-2.\nThen in the fourth,\nOliver Service\nand\nCleary Simpson\nled off the frame with a pair of walks. A one-out single to left by Golden loaded the bases and brought Bottone to the plate. After watching a ball, the center fielder launched the second pitch over the right-center fence to tie the game with a grand slam, 6-6, on his team-leading sixth long ball of the season.\nMU tallied another five runs in the seventh on a\nCooper Hinson\nRBI single, a Simpson bases-loaded walk and a bases-clearing three-RBI double from Smith to grab an 11-6 lead.\nTwo more runs crossed in the eighth with\nAJ Havrilla\ndrawing a one-out walk and scoring on a\nCam Harthan\ntriple with Service then bringing in Harthan on a sacrifice fly to cap off 13 unanswered runs.\nUP NEXT\nThe Herd is set to be back in action on Tuesday in Lexington, Kentucky, set for a contest set at 2 p.m. against the Wildcats.\nTo donate to the Championship Fund for Marshall baseball, please click\nHERE\n. All proceeds go directly to the Marshall baseball team.\nPar Mar is the presenting sponsor of the 2026 Marshall baseball team. Par Mar is the official convenience store of Marshall Athletics.\nFor all the latest information about Marshall baseball, follow @herdbaseball on Twitter and Instagram.\nTo follow all Thundering Herd sports and get live stats, schedules and free live audio, download the Marshall Athletics App for iOS and Android.\n---HerdZone.com---"
